Shaoyang diary
_
Shin-chan
_
_
_
_
_
_
My home is in Tangtian town, Shaoyang County, Hunan Province. On January 10, I returned home from my school in Guangzhou. Was ready to have a comfortable winter vacation, the result of the sudden outbreak of the disease so that everything around is no longer calm.
_
_
_
_
● Face Mask ● 
_
_
_
_
We have some face masks at home for my mother's work. But on January twenty-two, as the outbreak spread, I decided I didn't have enough masks, so I decided to go out and buy more. When I walked through town, there were very few people wearing masks on the road.

Walking into a pharmacy, I was told that it would cost two dollars to buy a disposable, generic surgical mask. I couldn't believe the price: "Two bucks a pop? " The clerk looked at me, smiled a little awkwardly, and then dodged my eyes. I decided to try another drugstore.

Fortunately, in another pharmacy, the boss said, their mask did not rise in price, as usual, a quarter. I bought one hundred and twenty quickly, thanked them and left.

At five o'clock in the afternoon, my sister also went out. She wanted to buy some masks for her friend in the county town, because they were not available in the county town at that time. But she only got forty masks after walking around the town.

Over the next day or two, my relatives learned that I had bought a mask and started asking me on Wechat if I could give them some because they could no longer buy one. In those two days, the town's masks had been swept away.
_
_
_
_
Do we or don't we
_
_
_
_
The elders of the family gradually realized the seriousness of the situation, but in the New Year's Eve, insisted on going out to pay New Year's greetings relatives or in the minority. Many of the elders'arguments focus on two aspects: First, are their own family members, will not do anything; second, we here, do not have to worry.
Under my persuasion and Popular Science, my parents finally agreed to minimize the number of trips. But it was not until the third day of the first lunar month that our family did not visit each other completely. Still, there are people near my home who are planning their daughter's first birthday party, as if they have no fear of the epidemic.
_
_
_
_
● video diary ● 

_
_
_
_
The video was taken on February 2, when I was walking around town and pedestrians were wearing masks. The town has very limited places of entertainment, and usually people like to stay in the river. But now the river is empty and there are significantly fewer pedestrians on the streets. Although the supermarket business as usual, but staff and customers are wearing masks, customers have significantly reduced. As I was leaving the supermarket, I heard a little girl ask the cashier if she could change the soda she had just bought because she found out that the bag was from Wuhan, Hubei Province.

I went to the market. The vendors are old people, and most of them don't wear masks. I asked an old man selling vegetables, "grandma, why don't you wear a mask? It's safer to wear a mask. " The old man took my concern as a reproach, with a very loud and very impolite answer: "No one hair mask, why do I wear? " After speaking, she looked around with a little smug. I was a little embarrassed to explain: "Now the virus is dangerous, you wear a mask would be safer. " The old man confidently replied: "I do not care, people are old, not afraid. " At this time another don not wear a mask to catch up with me: "Do you sell masks? "? How?"It's a paradox, it's safe to wear a mask, but you can't buy one, so you have to stay at home, but no food, no income..

Back Home, dad is on the phone, this is not know how many times he dissuaded his grandfather to go out for a stroll. "Life and death are up to us, " GRANDPA shouted from his cell phone. Dad and I had to be patient and reason with him. It wasn't just about his safety. It was about the health of everyone around him. For more than ten minutes, GRANDPA finally promised us not to go out again, he also told us that the village has been closed road. The villagers organized themselves to block the entrance of the village with trees to prevent outside vehicles from entering. I hung up the phone, and I thought, "I'm blocking the road. Isn't that a double-edged sword? "? I can't get out if it's an emergency! Is the worst thing you can do.

While I was typing on my computer, there was a gong outside, the staff was banging on the Gong to announce, don't go out, wear a mask. Just like I tell my family every day. The pace of the epidemic seems close.

My home is in Tangtian town, Shaoyang County, Hunan Province. On January 10, I returned home from my school in Guangzhou. Was ready to have a comfortable winter vacation, the result of the sudden outbreak of the disease so that everything around is no longer calm.

● video diary ● 

_
_
_
_
The video was taken on February 2, when I was walking around town and pedestrians were wearing masks. The town has very limited places of entertainment, and usually people like to stay in the river. But now the river is empty and there are significantly fewer pedestrians on the streets. Although the supermarket business as usual, but staff and customers are wearing masks, customers have significantly reduced. As I was leaving the supermarket, I heard a little girl ask the cashier if she could change the soda she had just bought because she found out that the bag was from Wuhan, Hubei Province.

I went to the market. The vendors are old people, and most of them don't wear masks. I asked an old man selling vegetables, "grandma, why don't you wear a mask? It's safer to wear a mask. " The old man took my concern as a reproach, with a very loud and very impolite answer: "No one hair mask, why do I wear? " After speaking, she looked around with a little smug. I was a little embarrassed to explain: "Now the virus is dangerous, you wear a mask would be safer. " The old man confidently replied: "I do not care, people are old, not afraid. " At this time another don not wear a mask to catch up with me: "Do you sell masks? "? How?"It's a paradox, it's safe to wear a mask, but you can't buy one, so you have to stay at home, but no food, no income..

Back Home, dad is on the phone, this is not know how many times he dissuaded his grandfather to go out for a stroll. "Life and death are up to us, " GRANDPA shouted from his cell phone. Dad and I had to be patient and reason with him. It wasn't just about his safety. It was about the health of everyone around him. For more than ten minutes, GRANDPA finally promised us not to go out again, he also told us that the village has been closed road. The villagers organized themselves to block the entrance of the village with trees to prevent outside vehicles from entering. I hung up the phone, and I thought, "I'm blocking the road. Isn't that a double-edged sword? "? I can't get out if it's an emergency! Is the worst thing you can do.

While I was typing on my computer, there was a gong outside, the staff was banging on the Gong to announce, don't go out, wear a mask. Just like I tell my family every day. The pace of the epidemic seems close.
